{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-14829/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-14829"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:48:29"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Man sits angrily at desk across from woman"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-14829","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-14829"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/canvas/1/8dc97188-5edf-4354-8311-f16367e4172f","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T18:54:51.499Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In this scene, where Reynolds thoughtlessly complains to Cyril that he does not like being \"turned away from,” ignoring the ways that he has done that very thing to her, his clothing is an almost perfect inverse of <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW42880460 BCX4\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-14842.html\"><u>hers</u></a>. He wears almost all white, while she is almost exclusively wearing navy blue. His navy bowtie matches her dress, and the white polka dots on it match the pearl necklace around her neck. The two siblings serve as mirrors of each other in this scene. While they are in many ways alike, and truly care for one another, in this conversation they are on opposing sides of a conflict.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:578.0381667993631,613.6639129674227,705.6112556402487,393.8582307427682"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/canvas/1/85abe158-d67f-496c-a500-d1c23b8d83fd","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T18:55:08.364Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Although the film ends in the mid-1960s, one of its central concerns is shifting styles and how Reynolds can keep pace—or not. As Cassie Davies-Strodder writes, “As the new decade [the 1960s]began, a number of couture houses were forced to close their doors as fashionable London shifted focus from the high-end couture of Mayfair to the irreverent youth fashions of the Kings Road and Carnaby Street. The new youth market coveted styles ‘bubbling up’ from the streets rather than those ‘trickling down’ from the wealthy elite and sounded the beginning of the end of the couture industry in London” (Davies-Strodder, “The New Bloom of Couture,” 18).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14829/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:68.36584394904456,54.386942675159204,336.38485270700625,227.14072452229289"}}}]}]}]}